---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-16 px-4 sm:px-6 text-white">
    <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-8">
      About Me
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-gray-300 text-lg leading-relaxed stagger-in">
      <p>
        Hey, I'm <strong class="text-white">Yash</strong>, a Cyber Security professional with a laser focus on <strong class="text-white">Data Leak Prevention (DLP)</strong> and the critical art of protecting data across every touchpoint — whether it's your endpoints, networks, or the cloud. My mission? To stop data theft before they start and ensure your sensitive information stays where it belongs.
      </p>

      <p>
        With hands-on expertise in building and deploying robust <strong class="text-white">DLP strategies</strong>, I design tailored solutions that not only safeguard data but also enhance regulatory compliance and streamline security practices across organizations. I don't just implement security solutions — I engineer them to fit your unique needs.
      </p>

      <p>
        Whether it's fortifying firewalls, securing networks, or locking down cloud environments, I bring deep expertise in <strong class="text-white">network security</strong> and <strong class="text-white">cloud defense</strong> to the table. And I'm always ahead of the curve, tracking the latest threats and trends, ensuring your defenses stay one step ahead of the bad actors.
      </p>

      <p>
        I live and breathe cyber security. From designing cutting-edge <strong class="text-white">DLP solutions</strong> to educating teams on best practices, I'm here to make sure your digital landscape is impenetrable.
      </p>

      <p>
        Ready to take your security to the next level? Let's connect and make it happen.
      </p>

      <p>
        Outside work, I like sharing knowledge, exploring places, travelling, and I'm passionate about cars and bikes.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
